==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overthwart
<hw>O"ver*thwart"</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"v⟦etil⟧r*thw⟦add⟧rt")</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a transverse position; placed or
situated across; hence, opposite.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Our <xex>overthwart</xex>
neighbors.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Crossing in kind or disposition; perverse; adverse;
opposing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Overthwart</xex> humor.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Clarendon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overthwart</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overthwart
<hw>O"ver*thwart"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Across; crosswise;
transversely.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Y'clenched <xex>overthwart</xex> and
endelong.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overthwart</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Overthwart
<hw>O"ver*thwart"</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>Across; from side to side
of.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Huge trees <xex>overthwart</xex> one another.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overthwart</ent>⟦br⟧

